The All Progressives Congress (APC), on Wednesday, took its presidential campaign to Enugu. Bola Tinubu, flagbearer of the party, also led APC members to pay a courtesy visit to Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi, the state governor. VIDEO: Tinubu takes presidential campaign to Enugu, pays courtesy visit to Ugwuanyi : @DOlusegun pic.twitter.com/Y9hbSzHEdL — TheCable (@thecableng) January 11, 2023  Ugwuanyi is a member of the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Also present with Tinubu were two APC governors — Hope Uzodimma of Imo and David Umahi of Ebonyi. Below are photos.            